recordings.loc: Rio Preto da Eva, State of Amazonas
recordings.rmk: The focal bird was recorded counter-singing, at times with a much more distant T. viridis, from the canopy of fairly mature secondary forest immediately adjacent to the Porto Alegre camp at the BDFFP. Noteworthy is a very long song at the 1:04 mark (effectively lasting 12 s!), which I think may have been two songs that were combined, as the bird appeared to momentarily lose steam mid-stream. Aside from normalizing, the recording was unaltered. This recording is also archived at the Macaulay Library (ML243766321).
